BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Academic,Lecture / Presentation / Talk
DESCRIPTION:Fr. Pat Hannon\, C.S.C.\, debuts his new book\, an incisive and
  ruminative From Glory to Glory: A Pilgrim’s Notes From the Badlands of Gra
 ce. Occasioned by the author’s walking\, with siblings\, the famous Camino 
 de Santiago in the fall of 2024\, the book traces all manner of other pilgr
 images—to and from home\, family\, love\, self\, and God. Each page shines 
 with the craft and vision of a spiritual essayist who has lived the insight
 s he has arrived at over more than three decades as a teacher\, writer\, pr
 eacher\, and pilgrim. At once a meditation on the Christian tradition regar
 ding pilgrimage as well as a reaching out to the broader cultural understan
 ding of that word\, Hannon’s book—which includes a foreword by acclaimed es
 sayist and biographer Michael N. McGregor—offers nourishment for all those 
 seeking wisdom for their own journeys.\n\nBio - Fr. Pat Hannon\, CSC\, is a
  senior instructor in the English department at the University of Portland.
  A graduate of the University of Portland (’82)\, he bleeds Purple and Whit
 e! Previous to From Glory to Glory\, Fr. Hannon has had seven collections o
 f essays published\, more recently\, Such Dizzy Natural Happiness: A Long\,
  Loving Look at the Lord’s Prayer (Chicago: ACTA Publications).\n\n \n\nCop
 ies of the book will be on sale at the event\, which includes a book signin
 g.\n\nCo-sponsored with the English Department. For more information or ADA
  accommodations: 503-943-7702 or garaventa@up.edu.
DTEND:20260311T011500Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T022535Z
DTSTART:20260311T000000Z
GEO:45.57252;-122.724823
LOCATION:Dundon-Berchtold Hall\, Brian Doyle Auditorium (DB004)
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Book Debut with Fr. Pat Hannon\, C.S.C.
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51763545239918
URL:https://calendar.up.edu/event/book-debut-with-fr-pat-hannon-csc
END:VEVENT
