BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Performance,Social Gathering / Reception
DESCRIPTION:Ticket show holders for UP's theater production of The Lightnin
 g Thief may enjoy a complimentary small bites reception and an expert pre-s
 how panel discussion. Ticket purchase HERE. Saturday\, April 18\, Mago Hunt
  Center. Reception at 6:15pm\; Panel Discussion from 6:45-7:15pm\; Show at 
 7:30pm. For more information and ADA accommodations contact garaventa@up.ed
 u and 503-943-7702.\n\nAbout The Lightning Thief: “As the half-blood son of
  a Greek god\, Percy Jackson has newly-discovered powers he can't control\,
  a destiny he doesn't want\, and a mythology textbook's worth of monsters o
 n his trail. When Zeus's master lightning bolt is stolen and Percy becomes 
 the prime suspect\, he has to find and return the bolt to prove his innocen
 ce and prevent a war between the gods…Adapted from the best-selling book Th
 e Lightning Thief by Rick Riordan and featuring a thrilling original rock s
 core\, The Lightning Thief: The Percy Jackson Musical is an action-packed m
 ythical adventure "worthy of the gods" (Time Out New York).
DTEND:20260419T021500Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T022535Z
DTSTART:20260419T011500Z
GEO:45.573252;-122.728181
LOCATION:Mago Hunt Center\, Lobby and Theater
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Theater Pre-Play Reception & Panel: "The Lightning Thief: The Percy
  Jackson Musical"
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51763879205860
URL:https://calendar.up.edu/event/copy-of-theater-pre-play-reception-panel-
 the-revolutionists
END:VEVENT
